    "created_at": "2013-11-06T01:28:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-11-06T01:28:27Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The last point really explains your dislike for the current approach and I completely agree with you.\nNobody wants to see a button for each action on every cell of the list. You may not notice it with one or two buttons\nbut when you add more actions (like Download, Rename, Open... just to mention some) it might result very difficult to use.\n\nThe other thing that might be an issue is that some actions make much more sense on one notebook than on a group of notebooks, like Rename. But that is the only one I can think of and is not even available on the dashboard right now.\nIt might be an option to have the checkbox driven UI for actions that apply to one or a group of notebooks (Delete, Download, Shutdown, Copy, Move) and a \"show on hover\" for things like Rename.\nDoes that sound confusing?\n"
  },
